##In the midst of an epidemic, Kuaishou stands watch

Lifeweek

Features an introduction to a magazine and the life he advocates.

_
2020 Lunar New Year, no festive Chinese New Year. Countless hearts were affected by the epidemic, Wuhan, Xiaogan, Huanggang, Suizhou, Jingzhou... many cities have launched a public health emergency response level one after another, a total of 34 provinces including Hubei, Guangdong and Zhejiang have reported cases of COVID-19.

As of February 8, there were 34,662 confirmed cases, 27,657 suspected cases, 6,101 serious cases, 724 deaths and 2,313 cured cases. It's a fight to the death.

When the affected cities were blockaded, masks, protective clothing, vegetables, fruits... even the Adult diaper were in emergency, countless people began to move to support the front-line medical staff, to support the suffering of the compatriots.

They come from different cities and have different careers. They are migrant workers, farmers, truck drivers, couriers, delivery workers... whether in the epidemic area or not, they go against the grain and become the guardians of the city, contributing to the city's functioning.

Tomatoes, cucumbers, garlic, Zucchini and sausage were loaded by the truckload, all destined for the same destination: Wuhan. The concern was simple, whether the people in the storm would be able to eat. In their eyes, "it's the best I can do as a normal person, " but it's also the harvest of their hard year.

In the quick hand, a hastily shouted "Wuhan refueling, China refueling, " a truck carrying supplies to Hubei, as well as the figure of delivery boy, always give comfort and warmth. The epidemic does not isolate the human heart, only action gives energy.

Speedy records the watchful hours of ordinary people, the courage to go to the front line, the recalcitrance of truck drivers, the loneliness of couriers on empty streets, and the optimism of isolation at home.

We firmly believe that records have power, and we will survive the battle without smoke. So, let's do it together.

Speed
"face life, full speed ahead. "

On January 28, a Sanla, who was traveling north and south, took a batch of goods to Wuhan. This is a batch of building materials sent to Wuhan Huoshenshan Hospital. The day is the third day of construction of the Vulcan Mountain Hospital, and in six days, the hospital will be put into use.

In front of the camera, he said, "for the first time with the owner of the goods, there is no calculation on the time, guaranteed full speed ahead. Before the price, time, but not today, facing life, the sooner delivered, the better. "

From Langfang in Hebei Province to Huoshen Mountain in Wuhan, it took Ah San 17 hours earlier than originally scheduled. Midway through, he rested for half an hour at the gas station. He knew that time was of the essence and that only "full speed ahead" was necessary.

After coming back from Wuhan, he contacted his hometown epidemic prevention station again at once and asked for quarantine. Although he could see his yard from the window of the isolation hospital, he chose isolation and "responsibility to his family" .

A three elder brothers in quick hand recorded the scene before leaving home. The younger son Clung to his father's thigh, full of attachment. Truck drivers running around all year round, not home, rarely home for the new year, it happened to encounter disaster. "I just want to set an example for my children, " he said. "That's what my father taught me. "

In Kuaishou, the truck drivers in the disaster relief area there are many, the destination is Wuhan. Cold storage driver Qiu Jie and her husband free delivery of vegetables for the Wuhan Union Hospital, Wuhan, when the fog filled, the two partner forward, a watch. After one trip, the two returned to Yunnan for a second support trip.

War
"from hospitals to the Internet, always on the front line. "

"Now we have arrived in Wuhan, look at my mask, inside and outside three layers Oh, two surgical masks an N95" , January 27, camouflage small nurses (round sugar) team released a video of medical staff landing in Wuhan.

Behind them, there are more like wearing camouflage clothes and masks to support the medical staff in Wuhan, to the center of the epidemic area.

Since the outbreak was released, a number of hospitals around the country sent medical teams to support Wuhan. On Feb. 7, the National Health and Human Services Commission said more than 11,000 health care workers had provided support. Say Goodbye to your children, say goodbye to your parents, and they show up where they are needed. Even if the mask out of the mark, but also adhere to the first line, in order to save patients.

At Kuaishou, Yu Changping, a respiratory surgeon at Wuhan University's People's Hospital, specializes in COVID-19.

He was the first member of the COVID-19 team to be infected and was being treated in isolation in an intensive care unit. He's got a funny way of saying things. He's got a local accent. Experts on the front lines are doing a quick science fair, which will no doubt end the public's fear of the virus.

He wants to do a little science at speedy, give you a sense of the disease and the epidemic. Because, "from the hospital to the Internet has been fighting in the front line. "

After he was hit by the Covid-19, Dr. Yu went into a coma and was almost on his deathbed. But his faith in his own physical strength and will power kept him on the mend.

For the front-line Medical Staff, Dr. Yu did not know when the infection, who was infected. But he said, when I get out of here, I'm GonNa keep working on the patient.

Indeed, the fight against the virus is a tug of war, with active protection and scientific understanding essential. Thank you to the medical staff who fought on the front line. Thank you for your persistence.

Speed
Behind the "China speed"

Ma Liye is a salesman in Shandong Electric Vehicle Company. This Spring Festival, he became a volunteer at Wuhan Huoshenshan Hospital to help with hospital construction.

On January 23, the day before New Year's Eve, he recorded jokes in the fast hand, indicating that he would continue to take orders during the Spring Festival. Five days later, he photographed Wuhan's empty streets and high-rise buildings and said, "Go Wuhan, I'm coming. "

The Construction Day is overtime, day and night. Ma often posts short videos in the wee hours of the morning. In the camera, the construction site of the Fire God Mountain Hospital is still busy, with the thundering of the crane and the workers carrying building materials and building ventilation ducts outside. After a hard day's work, he sat on the curb and gulped down his boxed lunch!

Working overtime to deliver on time. On the morning of February 2, the 30,000 square meter, 1,000 bed Gross leasable area was officially handed over to the People's army medical workers, and the next day the COVID-19 was officially admitted to treat patients with pneumonia.

In the video, Ma says that "the record is to leave a witness. ". He witnessed the "Chinese speed" of building a hospital in 10 days. In the quick hands of Ma and the migrant workers, these anonymous figures of labor are recorded, their fatigue and sweat deserve to be recorded and praised.

This is a testament to the power of the Working People.

Decided
"Do your best as an ordinary person. "

After nine days of struggle, 10,000 Jin of carrots were finally donated. On January 29, Great Dandan in Xiqing District, Tianjin, discovered the outbreak and wanted to donate 10,000 catties of turnips from their farmland to the disaster area as a token of their love.

Brother and sister in Kuaishou issued a request for help, hoping to have a free car of the caring people will be turnip transport to Wuhan. After contacting the vehicle, the family started loading the turnips. At the time, they had not been told that private transport was no longer possible to reach the affected areas, and that pipelines had given way to medical supplies and institutional transport.

After knowing the news, the family was anxious to contact other vehicles. Among them toss and turn hard to predict, they encountered doubt and misunderstanding, also encountered false charity of show. The family, who had intended only to donate the turnips, did not anticipate that "it would be so hard to do good" .

Two and a half days of being misunderstood and questioned is hard. Dandan in quick hand recalled, "midnight more than 12 o'clock, although tired but still unable to sleep, uneasy in the heart, afraid of not finding the car, afraid of being misunderstood, also afraid of these two and a half days of effort to naught. "

The turnips were donated to the Heping District Red Cross in Tianjin. What supports them is the loving message under the video, which encourages and supports them.

In the village of Potou in Hekou County, Honghe Hani and Yi Autonomous Prefecture province, 93 families donated 22 tons of bananas to the city. The mountain road is difficult to drive, the villagers will ride a motorcycle will be a basket of bananas transported to the concentration point, and then a unified car to Wuhan.

A brother of Rizhao Green tea donated 3000 catties of tomatoes to Wuhan, and a basket of tomatoes was sent to Wuhan overnight by special bus. "strong contribution" , in the eyes of a brother, this is his best efforts as an ordinary person.

Diary of Wuhan City

It was the 17th day of the siege of Wuhan. Wuhan bus, subway system has been suspended, coupled with private cars ban, the former bustling, bustling city quickly quiet, crowded streets are empty, no vehicles pass.

Through speedy's town, fortunately the city hasn't been shut down by the outbreak. Outside the isolation of the home, people struggle to maintain daily life, with optimism and confidence to establish order in life, not to be overwhelmed by panic.

Wuhan Railway Station Staff "you go you call Zuo Shuang" busy for a year, just ready to go home for the New Year, because of the epidemic hit, consider the safety of family members, ready not to go home. He graduated in 2019, his first year on the job. He took snapshots of Wuhan Railway Station and himself at work, cheering for Wuhan and cheering for himself. He said, "the current health, please rest assured that family and friends! "

In Wuhan, there are still couriers and deliverymen at work. Yuan Shuang, a courier, was carrying a box of goods down an empty street. "there is no one in the neighborhood except me, " he quipped. To avoid infection, contactless delivery is now advocated. A family handed out a mask, a "thank you" can make him happy for a long time.

The noisy streets had become cold, making the delivery boy feel strange. They get lonely, too. "There's no one here, there's no one on the street, " a delivery man sobbed. "I feel terrible. I'm on my bike and I'm crying. "

There are vegetable farmers in the stall, the elderly wearing a mask, guarding the wholesale scallions, vegetables, put a long time will rot.

The Finnish queuing method is popular in the streets, where people stand a meter apart at the entrance of the supermarket, waiting to enter the supermarket. Some of the citizens brought their own goggles. People began to help each other, buy large quantities of goods together, and then distribute them to citizens who could not go out to shop.

Residents in the affected areas left a section of the city in Kuaishou diary, Short but simple. Take a mask to the supermarket to buy food, before entering the home body disinfection, but also the occasional joy in distress. Even if it is just a Three Meals a Day, the smiling faces of family members, it is also a way for people to keep an eye on each other to say "peace" , life is still good.

The fourth day of the city closure in Wuhan is also the 38th day of "simple sister Jin" doing Yuezi. Her Second Darling was born. She was separated from her husband and children at home. January 30, the haze for a few days in Wuhan out of the Sun, Sister Jin also want to go out for a walk.

In the same city diary, she wrote, today the weather is very good, the sun is warm, if it is normal, the beach must have a lot of people bask in the Sun, kite flying, love

With the epidemic, the old walks were a luxury. Speedy city is a cyber city, documenting the daily routines of residents in the affected areas outside the empty streets, both tense and relaxed. Records will not stop, this is our voice to each other, each other's watch, to the affected area of the people to bring warmth and comfort.

Say Again, go Wuhan, Go China.

A brother of Rizhao Green tea donated 3000 catties of tomatoes to Wuhan, and a basket of tomatoes was sent to Wuhan overnight by special bus. "strong contribution" , in the eyes of a brother, this is his best efforts as an ordinary person.

Diary of Wuhan City

It was the 17th day of the siege of Wuhan. Wuhan bus, subway system has been suspended, coupled with private cars ban, the former bustling, bustling city quickly quiet, crowded streets are empty, no vehicles pass.

Through speedy's town, fortunately the city hasn't been shut down by the outbreak. Outside the isolation of the home, people struggle to maintain daily life, with optimism and confidence to establish order in life, not to be overwhelmed by panic.

Wuhan Railway Station Staff "you go you call Zuo Shuang" busy for a year, just ready to go home for the New Year, because of the epidemic hit, consider the safety of family members, ready not to go home. He graduated in 2019, his first year on the job. He took snapshots of Wuhan Railway Station and himself at work, cheering for Wuhan and cheering for himself. He said, "the current health, please rest assured that family and friends! "

In Wuhan, there are still couriers and deliverymen at work. Yuan Shuang, a courier, was carrying a box of goods down an empty street. "there is no one in the neighborhood except me, " he quipped. To avoid infection, contactless delivery is now advocated. A family handed out a mask, a "thank you" can make him happy for a long time.

The noisy streets had become cold, making the delivery boy feel strange. They get lonely, too. "There's no one here, there's no one on the street, " a delivery man sobbed. "I feel terrible. I'm on my bike and I'm crying. "

There are vegetable farmers in the stall, the elderly wearing a mask, guarding the wholesale scallions, vegetables, put a long time will rot.

The Finnish queuing method is popular in the streets, where people stand a meter apart at the entrance of the supermarket, waiting to enter the supermarket. Some of the citizens brought their own goggles. People began to help each other, buy large quantities of goods together, and then distribute them to citizens who could not go out to shop.

Residents in the affected areas left a section of the city in Kuaishou diary, Short but simple. Take a mask to the supermarket to buy food, before entering the home body disinfection, but also the occasional joy in distress. Even if it is just a Three Meals a Day, the smiling faces of family members, it is also a way for people to keep an eye on each other to say "peace" , life is still good.

The fourth day of the city closure in Wuhan is also the 38th day of "simple sister Jin" doing Yuezi. Her Second Darling was born. She was separated from her husband and children at home. January 30, the haze for a few days in Wuhan out of the Sun, Sister Jin also want to go out for a walk.

In the same city diary, she wrote, today the weather is very good, the sun is warm, if it is normal, the beach must have a lot of people bask in the Sun, kite flying, love

With the epidemic, the old walks were a luxury. Speedy city is a cyber city, documenting the daily routines of residents in the affected areas outside the empty streets, both tense and relaxed. Records will not stop, this is our voice to each other, each other's watch, to the affected area of the people to bring warmth and comfort.

Say Again, go Wuhan, Go China.

2020 Lunar New Year, no festive Chinese New Year. Countless hearts were affected by the epidemic, Wuhan, Xiaogan, Huanggang, Suizhou, Jingzhou... many cities have launched a public health emergency response level one after another, a total of 34 provinces including Hubei, Guangdong and Zhejiang have reported cases of COVID-19.

As of February 8, there were 34,662 confirmed cases, 27,657 suspected cases, 6,101 serious cases, 724 deaths and 2,313 cured cases. It's a fight to the death.

When the affected cities were blockaded, masks, protective clothing, vegetables, fruits... even the Adult diaper were in emergency, countless people began to move to support the front-line medical staff, to support the suffering of the compatriots.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
They come from different cities and have different careers. They are migrant workers, farmers, truck drivers, couriers, delivery workers... whether in the epidemic area or not, they go against the grain and become the guardians of the city, contributing to the city's functioning.

Tomatoes, cucumbers, garlic, Zucchini and sausage were loaded by the truckload, all destined for the same destination: Wuhan. The concern was simple, whether the people in the storm would be able to eat. In their eyes, "it's the best I can do as a normal person, " but it's also the harvest of their hard year.

After coming back from Wuhan, he contacted his hometown epidemic prevention station again at once and asked for quarantine. Although he could see his yard from the window of the isolation hospital, he chose isolation and "responsibility to his family" .

Behind the "China speed"

Behind the "China speed"

Ma Liye is a salesman in Shandong Electric Vehicle Company. This Spring Festival, he became a volunteer at Wuhan Huoshenshan Hospital to help with hospital construction.

On January 23, the day before New Year's Eve, he recorded jokes in the fast hand, indicating that he would continue to take orders during the Spring Festival. Five days later, he photographed Wuhan's empty streets and high-rise buildings and said, "Go Wuhan, I'm coming. "

The Construction Day is overtime, day and night. Ma often posts short videos in the wee hours of the morning. In the camera, the construction site of the Fire God Mountain Hospital is still busy, with the thundering of the crane and the workers carrying building materials and building ventilation ducts outside. After a hard day's work, he sat on the curb and gulped down his boxed lunch!

"Do your best as an ordinary person. "

After nine days of struggle, 10,000 Jin of carrots were finally donated. On January 29, Great Dandan in Xiqing District, Tianjin, discovered the outbreak and wanted to donate 10,000 catties of turnips from their farmland to the disaster area as a token of their love.

Brother and sister in Kuaishou issued a request for help, hoping to have a free car of the caring people will be turnip transport to Wuhan. After contacting the vehicle, the family started loading the turnips. At the time, they had not been told that private transport was no longer possible to reach the affected areas, and that pipelines had given way to medical supplies and institutional transport.
